# Security headers for the static site. Review CSP changes before deploy.
#
# 2026-05-13 static security header update:
#   - Added upgrade-insecure-requests: silently re-issues any mixed-content sub-resource
#     over HTTPS (belt+suspenders with HSTS preload).
#   - Added Cross-Origin-Resource-Policy / Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: blocks Spectre-style
#     side-channel embeds + window.opener leak from popup-based phishing.
#   - Added X-Permitted-Cross-Domain-Policies: none — disables legacy Flash/Acrobat policy
#     file discovery on this origin.
#   - Tightened Permissions-Policy: 22-feature explicit opt-out (was 3). All disabled — we
#     ship no UA-feature-using code on the static site. Adds payment=() so an injected
#     card-stealer script can't summon a PaymentRequest dialog. fullscreen=(self) is the only
#     feature that's "self" rather than "()" so a hypothetical future status-page expand-on-
#     click can still go fullscreen on the user's own click; today no site/*.html uses it.
#   - Kept 'unsafe-inline' in script-src / style-src: 27 site/*.html files carry inline
#     <script> bodies (event handlers / SSR data hydration / status polling) + 34 carry
#     inline <style>. Full unsafe-inline removal is a separate lane (see RESIDUAL DEBT
#     comment below — would require hash-pinning every inline block or extracting all into
#     /static/*.js + /static/*.css, both high-churn vs static-site benefit).
#   - Kept hash-pinned script-src in CSP-Report-Only as the migration target — the 6 sha256
#     hashes already cover the load-bearing inline blocks; expand the list as we extract
#     more inline scripts.
#
# RESIDUAL DEBT (track in audit; do not silently expand without re-pinning hashes):
#   - 27 site/*.html files with inline <script> bodies (excluding type=application/ld+json
#     which is non-executable JSON-LD and CSP-exempt).
#   - 34 site/*.html files with inline <style> bodies.
#   - 3 site/*.html files with inline event handlers (onclick=/onsubmit=/onload=): login.html,
#     dashboard.html, bookmarklet.html.
#   Goal: drive both counts to 0 in a dedicated lane, then strip 'unsafe-inline' from
#   script-src and style-src in the enforcing CSP above.
/*
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' https://plausible.io https://static.cloudflareinsights.com; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; img-src 'self' data: https:; font-src 'self' data:; connect-src 'self' https://api.jpcite.com https://pypi.org https://plausible.io https://cloudflareinsights.com; frame-src 'none'; frame-ancestors 'none'; object-src 'none'; base-uri 'self'; form-action 'self' https://checkout.stripe.com https://billing.stripe.com; upgrade-insecure-requests
  Content-Security-Policy-Report-Only: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self' 'sha256-0LkrXXIDvlJXDyiVMzXgmEl9qUbtOjoKDx3IC87K8bY=' 'sha256-1TFHSaz1uwUQa0945e71hEHJEzuJjt/CNaWnWsvpSvo=' 'sha256-AJtTnpCPsluvn5R8eQuYalW6heCXkU6dk1zmth/oITQ=' 'sha256-otI9BoZyeDx91z2i6bqiMURDUX1T5yXR+T7rTExOD3w=' 'sha256-oz2/C7uS96S5tB0l5gMxl8QG2Dfc7vQde6m+gn5CjZM=' 'sha256-sJV/8gAIT9L3t693bKuhv84h/vMPAT/WmmgGKWpwEH0=' https://plausible.io https://static.cloudflareinsights.com; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; img-src 'self' data: https:; font-src 'self' data:; connect-src 'self' https://api.jpcite.com https://pypi.org https://plausible.io https://cloudflareinsights.com; frame-src 'none'; frame-ancestors 'none'; object-src 'none'; base-uri 'self'; form-action 'self' https://checkout.stripe.com https://billing.stripe.com; upgrade-insecure-requests
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains; preload
  Permissions-Policy: accelerometer=(), ambient-light-sensor=(), autoplay=(), battery=(), camera=(), display-capture=(), document-domain=(), encrypted-media=(), fullscreen=(self), geolocation=(), gyroscope=(), magnetometer=(), microphone=(), midi=(), payment=(), picture-in-picture=(), publickey-credentials-get=(), screen-wake-lock=(), sync-xhr=(), usb=(), web-share=(), xr-spatial-tracking=()
