# companion Markdown — companion-Markdown surface (GitHub-style `{url}.md`).
# Every public SEO HTML page (cases / laws / enforcement) ships a sibling
# `.md` file that contains the same canonical narrative as Markdown with
# YAML-ish frontmatter (canonical / lang / est_tokens / source_url / fetched_at).
# These are the LLM citation crawl surface — many 2026 answer engines refuse
# JS-heavy HTML and ingest only `{url}.md` when present. Cloudflare Pages must
# serve them as `text/markdown` so the crawler does not fall back to
# `application/octet-stream`. UTF-8 charset is required for JA text.
# Long edge cache because the .md companion files are refreshed together;
# downstream LLMs benefit from a stable corpus snapshot.
/cases/*.md
  Content-Type: text/markdown; charset=utf-8
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=86400, stale-while-revalidate=604800
  X-Robots-Tag: index, follow

/laws/*.md
  Content-Type: text/markdown; charset=utf-8
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=86400, stale-while-revalidate=604800
  X-Robots-Tag: index, follow

/enforcement/*.md
  Content-Type: text/markdown; charset=utf-8
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=86400, stale-while-revalidate=604800
  X-Robots-Tag: index, follow

