# citation substrate for answer engines, but Cloudflare Pages does not
# emit X-Robots-Tag by default — without an explicit "index, follow"
# header the per-row HTML can drop out of Bing / DuckAssist / GPT search
# indexes if a CDN-injected header collides. The header below is belt-
# and-suspenders to the in-page <meta name="robots" content="index,
# follow"> already present in the row templates.
# Cache profile (browser 1 day / edge 1 week) matches the rest of the
# per-row SEO group and is conservative enough that any copy fix
